who run the hedgehog over by asda as i was driving home yesterday i saw a baby hedgehog crossing the road it was broad daylight i stopped to let it cross and the car coming in the opposite direction stopped also when it was almost on the kerb i carried on home this morning when i went past it was squashed in the road poor thing will his family miss him thanks no i am asparagus i hope so ah well whenever you see a baby hedgehog or indeed any hedgehog out during daylight hours then you should pick it up and rescue him any animal that is nocturnal only comes out at bnight time that is seen out during the day time has something wrong it could be for a number of reasons when you pick up a hedgehog in this situation be sure to keep it warm by putting a hot water bottle in a box lined with newspaper then you must contact your local wildlife carer or rspca centre if you need any more help in the future you can contact me at blyth wildlife rescue or the british hedgehog preservation society who will be able to give you any advice required Sonic the Hedgehog Daylight saving time Sonic the Hedgehog (16-bit) Hedgehog Criticism of government response to Hurricane Katrina Rules of the road Breastfeeding Sonic the Hedgehog 2 USS Waters (DD-115) Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Escape from New York Civil engineering and infrastructure repair in New Orleans after Hurricane Katrina Chaos Emerald Indianapolis 500 Fire fighting USS Whale (SS-239) Caving USS Sea Dog (SS-401) Solar power Sega Mina Mongoose Paul Is Dead Rail terminology Adventures of Sonic the Hedgehog Sonic the Hedgehog (Archie) USS Ammen (DD-527) USS Wickes (DD-578) Jon Secada Sonic the Hedgehog 3 Social rule Mario Toronto Subway and RT Energy development Shadow the Hedgehog Hampton Roads USS Anderson (DD-411) Golf Pet skunk USS Yorktown (CV-5) Doctor Eggman Ecco the Dolphin Driver's license Jackass: The Movie Light rail Poker jargon Minor characters in Sonic the Hedgehog The Amazing Race Fox hunting Sonic Adventure James Ha